txt.en: Siege engines and banners can be found in the encampment of Urûshoba.\n\nYou should destroy siege engines and banners.
<rgb=#FF0000>Completing 'Restoring the Three Kingdoms' will cancel this quest</rgb>
You have destroyed many siege engines and banners.
Siege engines and banners can be found in the encampment of Urûshoba.\n\nYou should destroy siege engines and banners.

'It would appear the Jangovar have begun to rebuild Urûshoba once again. The strategic location of their encampment has been nothing but trouble for the peoples of the North, and we cannot allow them to regain a foothold in the Dale-lands.\n\n'Travel to Urûshoba, throw down their banners, and ruin their siege equipment. Do this, and you will have my thanks.'
The Jangovar encampment of Urûshoba struggles to rebuild enough to set siege to the Dale-lands once more.
You have destroyed many siege engines and banners in the Jangovar encampment of Urûshoba. You have dealt a terrible blow to the Jangovar's efforts to rebuild.
